just some random thoughts

=2E  wait til morning, but disconnect battery tonight,
=2E  Fuel Injection has a certain minimum voltage to operate (can't remembe=
r
what it is off the top of my head, around 9 volts I think
=2E  it sounds like you have some sort of short circuit, probably through
something
=2E  in the morning charge battery.
    -take all your fuses out, mark em!
    -put an ammeter between your battery + terminal and the main wire
    -make sure ammeter reads 0  if not find problem
    -put fuses back in one at a time and see when the meter jumps
    -when you find circuit trace  wires in that circuit
    =20
intermittent electrical problems are some of the most perplexing

